data.meta_description: DN5 0EP is a primarily residential postcode in Bentley, Doncaster. Check typical house prices, council tax bands, business rates, broadband availability and local schools. Find nearby hotels and holiday rentals.
data.text:
Summary

DN5 0EP is a primarily residential postcode in Bentley, Doncaster. It was first introduced in January 1980.

The most common council tax band is A.

Residential buildings are primarily terraced (including end-terrace). Domestic properties are primarily houses.

Estimated residential property values, based on historical transactions and adjusted for inflation, range from £39,966 to £247,146 with an average of £112,506.

Residential buildings were typically constructed between 1900 and 1929.

None of the residential properties sold since 1995 have been new builds or newly converted.

Domestic properties are mostly a mix of social housing and owner occupied.

The most common Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) ratings are D and E.

Commercial rateable values range from £2,075 to £10,500 with an average of £5,269. The most common recorded business types are Vehicle Repair Workshop and Car Display Site.

Bentley is a town, which had a population of 27,145 in the 2011 census.

In the 2011 census, there were 74 people resident in DN5 0EP, of which 40 were male and 34 were female. This also includes overnight visitors at domestic properties, and residents of non-domestic properties such as hotels, prisons and halls of residence.

DN5 0EP is in the Doncaster travel to work area. NHS services are provided by the Doncaster Primary Care Trust.

DN5 0EP is approximately 8m (26ft) above sea level.
